-- Kobe Yakuza Office Hit by Blast in First Attack Since 1993, Yomiuri Says
-- B y   M a s a t s u g u   H o r i e
-- 2010-11-01T03:53:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/kobe-yakuza-office-hit-by-blast-in-first-attack-since-1993-yomiuri-says.html
An explosion occurred early this
morning outside the head office of a Kobe-based affiliate of the
Yamaguchi Gumi, Japan’s biggest organized crime group, the
Yomiuri newspaper reported.  The blast, the first such attack since 1993 against a
headquarters of the yakuza crime group, broke windows in the
Yamaken Gumi’s office and surrounding houses in the western city,
the Yomiuri said, citing local police. There were no injuries,
the report said  Yamaken, Yamaguchi Gumi’s largest affiliate, has about
4,000 members, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Masatsugu Horie  in Osaka at 
 mhorie3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Drew Gibson in Osaka at 
 dgibson2@bloomberg.net . 